From Steven J Orlin Subject Re Changing oil by In article Grays on Walker writes Why crawl under the car at all I have a machine I got for my boat that pulls the oil out under suction through the dip stick It does an excellent job and by moving the suction tube around you can get more old oil out than by using the drain I think I paid at E B The oil goes into a steel gal can wait until it cools and decant into your favorite I use soft drink Easy to take them down to the local oil recycle Yeah I suppose you could do But then you don't get the broken knuckles the rust in your eyes the oil bath and the burns from the I mean come on Steve